Preheat the grill to the highest setting.For the roasted goats' cheese, mix together the breadcrumbs, fresh parsley and fresh rosemary and season, to taste, with salt and freshly ground black pepper.Dip the cut side of the halved goats' cheese into the breadcrumb mix and press on well to ensure a good coating. Place onto a baking sheet and place under the grill for 6-8 minutes, or until melted slightly and turning golden brown.To make the salad, mix all the salad ingredients together in a bowl.To serve, place a pile of the salad onto a plate and place the roasted goats' cheese on top.